##Phishing Attacks

#### Look through Sofia's emails below and see which ones might be legit and which might be phishing attacks.

<div style="font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6;">


  <hr>

  <p><strong>Message A – Text</strong></p>
  <p>
    Hey Sofia — it’s Jada from dance club!<br><br>
    We’re putting together a BTS medley for the showcase and need everyone’s shirt sizes.<br><br>
    Can you send yours so we can order matching tops?
  </p>

  <hr>

  <p><strong>Message B – Email</strong></p>
  <p><em>Subject:</em> <strong>BTS Fan Box Shipping Confirmation</strong></p>
  <p>
    Hi Sofia,<br><br>
    You’re receiving this email because you signed up for BTS fan rewards through one of our partners.<br>
    Your VIP Fan Box includes exclusive merch and early livestream access.<br><br>
    To confirm shipping, please verify your name, birthdate, and mailing address:<br>
    <a href="#">fanportal.bts-box.com</a><br><br>
    If we don’t hear from you in 24 hours, your spot may be reassigned.<br><br>
    Thanks,<br>
    <em>The Fan Box Team</em>
  </p>

  <hr>

  <p><strong>Message C – Instagram DM</strong></p>
  <p>
    <strong>From: @miamijuiceguide</strong><br><br>
    Hey Sofia! We saw your post about your family’s juice bar!<br>
    We’re featuring small Miami businesses on our food blog this month.<br><br>
    If you’re the owner or a family member, reply with your contact number, email, and home address so we can arrange an interview & feature you!
  </p>

</div>

##Breach Reports 
#### A data breach is a security incident where sensitive, confidential, or private information is accessed, disclosed, or stolen by unauthorized individuals.

#### Look through Sofia's breach report to try to determine what happened and what type of password attack your user was vulnerable to.

<div style="font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6;">

  <h3 style="color: #00838f;">Breach Report</h3>
  <p><strong>Service Breached:</strong> School Email Portal<br>
     <strong>Login Location:</strong> IP masked via VPN (region unknown)<br>
     <strong>Time of Access:</strong> 6:58 a.m.<br>
     <strong>AI Analysis:</strong> Normal login activity for this account begins after 8:15 a.m.
  </p>

  <p>Multiple student accounts were targeted in a short time frame.<br>
     Several short sessions were initiated across different usernames.<br>
     Sofia’s account was accessed using the password: <strong>BTS123</strong><br>
     There was no prior login history from the device used.
  </p>

  <p><strong>AI Analysis:</strong> Password matched a set of interest-themed patterns attempted across multiple accounts.<br>
     The attacker viewed calendar events but did not send or delete any messages.<br>
     <strong>AI Analysis:</strong> Browser language settings during login were set to Spanish, which differs from the account default.
  </p>

  <br>

  <h3 style="color: #00838f;">Password Attacks</h3>

  <table style="width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; border:1px solid #ccc; font-size: 15px;">
    <tr>
      <td style="font-weight:bold; padding:10px; border:1px solid #ccc;">Credential stuffing attack</td>
      <td style="padding:10px; border:1px solid #ccc;">
        When attackers use real usernames and passwords (often from past breaches) to break into other accounts.
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="font-weight:bold; padding:10px; border:1px solid #ccc;">Password guessing attack</td>
      <td style="padding:10px; border:1px solid #ccc;">
        When attackers try different passwords for one account, hoping to guess the right one.
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="font-weight:bold; padding:10px; border:1px solid #ccc;">Password spraying attack</td>
      <td style="padding:10px; border:1px solid #ccc;">
        When an attacker tries one common password on many different accounts to avoid detection.
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="font-weight:bold; padding:10px; border:1px solid #ccc;">Brute force attack</td>
      <td style="padding:10px; border:1px solid #ccc;">
        When an attacker rapidly tries a large number of possible passwords on one account, using automated tools to find the correct one.
      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>

</div>

